{"title":"Blender tutorial: selecting and transforming objects","description":"Second post of the Blender tutorial series. This time we will learn how to select and move objects.","date":"17 Feb 2018","readingTime":"4 min read","featuredImageUrl":"/static/53ecaf5d4bd48177bcdae6c5ae3c809a/blender-selecting-objects-2.jpg","authors":["fabrizio_duroni"],"tags":["computer graphics","blender"],"math":false,"content":"<p><em>Second post of the \"Blender tutorial\" series. This time we will learn how to select and move objects.</em></p>\n<hr>\n<p>In\nthe <a href=\"/2018/01/31/blender-tutorial-1-user-interface/\" title=\"Blender tutorial:user interface\">first post of the \"Blender tutorial\" series</a>\nwe learned how the user interface is composed and the most important commands to navigate inside a scene. This time we\nwill be focus on selecting and moving objects inside the 3D view.<br>\nWe can <strong>select an object</strong> by using the <em>right button of your mouse</em>. If you're on the MacBook like me, the right mouse\nis emulated in some ways (my personal preferences is to use two fingers to emulate a right click). To <em>select multiple\nobjects</em> we can hold the <em>shift button and select with a right click the objects</em> we want. The objects that we will\nselect will be marked in the outliner editor, with a little circle, and in the 3D view with a little border. The color\nof the border will change based on the theme you selected. In the screenshot below we can see that I selected 2 of the 3\nobjects in the scene. If we have multiple objects selected, the last one will have a different border. In my case the\ncube is the last object selected.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/8ca21f3d1d02bf825e6018ce24ed193b/c58a3/blender-selecting-objects-1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.859649122807014%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Object selection in Blender\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/8ca21f3d1d02bf825e6018ce24ed193b/0470c/blender-selecting-objects-1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/8ca21f3d1d02bf825e6018ce24ed193b/6c669/blender-selecting-objects-1.jpg 285w,\n/static/8ca21f3d1d02bf825e6018ce24ed193b/882a4/blender-selecting-objects-1.jpg 570w,\n/static/8ca21f3d1d02bf825e6018ce24ed193b/0470c/blender-selecting-objects-1.jpg 1140w,\n/static/8ca21f3d1d02bf825e6018ce24ed193b/c58a3/blender-selecting-objects-1.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Object selection in Blender</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>To deselect an object we can just right click on it again. We can also <strong>select all the objects</strong> in a scene, including\ncameras and lights, by pressing the <em>\"a\" key</em>.<br>\nThere's also a select menu that gives us more control over the selections we can do. In particular, we have the <strong>Circle\nselect</strong>, that lets us select objects based on a circle pattern of selection, and the <strong>Border select</strong>, that lets us\nselect objects based on a squared pattern of selection. There are also other option to select random objects or invert\nthe current selection.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/53ecaf5d4bd48177bcdae6c5ae3c809a/c58a3/blender-selecting-objects-2.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.859649122807014%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Selection menu in Blender\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/53ecaf5d4bd48177bcdae6c5ae3c809a/0470c/blender-selecting-objects-2.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/53ecaf5d4bd48177bcdae6c5ae3c809a/6c669/blender-selecting-objects-2.jpg 285w,\n/static/53ecaf5d4bd48177bcdae6c5ae3c809a/882a4/blender-selecting-objects-2.jpg 570w,\n/static/53ecaf5d4bd48177bcdae6c5ae3c809a/0470c/blender-selecting-objects-2.jpg 1140w,\n/static/53ecaf5d4bd48177bcdae6c5ae3c809a/c58a3/blender-selecting-objects-2.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Selection menu in Blender</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>To <strong>translate objects</strong>, we can use the transform tools. We can find them under <em>Tools -> Transform</em>. As a consequence\nof the fact that we are trying to translate an object in 3D space using the mouse pointer that works in 2D space, it is\ndifficult to understand in which direction we are doing our translation. We can <strong>constraint the move</strong> to just one axis\nby pressing:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>\"x\" key</em> for the x axis</li>\n<li><em>\"y\" key</em> for the y axis</li>\n<li><em>\"z\" key</em> for the z axis</li>\n</ul>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4e7c88ec3a9bdadaa599e6fa43a59346/c58a3/blender-translating-objects-1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.859649122807014%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Translation of objects in Blender\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/4e7c88ec3a9bdadaa599e6fa43a59346/0470c/blender-translating-objects-1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4e7c88ec3a9bdadaa599e6fa43a59346/6c669/blender-translating-objects-1.jpg 285w,\n/static/4e7c88ec3a9bdadaa599e6fa43a59346/882a4/blender-translating-objects-1.jpg 570w,\n/static/4e7c88ec3a9bdadaa599e6fa43a59346/0470c/blender-translating-objects-1.jpg 1140w,\n/static/4e7c88ec3a9bdadaa599e6fa43a59346/c58a3/blender-translating-objects-1.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Translation of objects in Blender</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>There's also the possibility to move an object with discrete values by using its location properties panel under the\nproperties editor or using the object properties panel in the 3D window. Finally we can move objects using also the 3D\nmanipulator widget in the 3D window. We can activate it by pressing on its icon. After that when you select and object\nyou will see three axes. Drag one of them to translate the object in that direction.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/529932ec7fb0ef02ee706b1f236856f4/c58a3/blender-translating-objects-2.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.859649122807014%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Moving objects in Blender\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/529932ec7fb0ef02ee706b1f236856f4/0470c/blender-translating-objects-2.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/529932ec7fb0ef02ee706b1f236856f4/6c669/blender-translating-objects-2.jpg 285w,\n/static/529932ec7fb0ef02ee706b1f236856f4/882a4/blender-translating-objects-2.jpg 570w,\n/static/529932ec7fb0ef02ee706b1f236856f4/0470c/blender-translating-objects-2.jpg 1140w,\n/static/529932ec7fb0ef02ee706b1f236856f4/c58a3/blender-translating-objects-2.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Moving objects in Blender</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>We can rotate and scaling an object using the same tools we used for the translation:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>the transformation tools</li>\n<li>the 3D manipulator widget</li>\n</ul>\n<p>One important thing to consider when we are working with transformation is the transform orientation. This option\ndefines the orientation of the transform operation. This is very important because it influences the final result of the\ntransform operation. You can change the transform orientation in the 3D manipulator widget.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/bfb8354aa1917560c63e8a9c740c9360/c58a3/blender-translating-objects-3.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.859649122807014%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"3D manipulator widget\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/bfb8354aa1917560c63e8a9c740c9360/0470c/blender-translating-objects-3.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/bfb8354aa1917560c63e8a9c740c9360/6c669/blender-translating-objects-3.jpg 285w,\n/static/bfb8354aa1917560c63e8a9c740c9360/882a4/blender-translating-objects-3.jpg 570w,\n/static/bfb8354aa1917560c63e8a9c740c9360/0470c/blender-translating-objects-3.jpg 1140w,\n/static/bfb8354aa1917560c63e8a9c740c9360/c58a3/blender-translating-objects-3.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">3D manipulator widget</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>The 3D manipulator widget will place the start of the <strong>transform based on the origin of an objects</strong>. We can <strong>change\nit</strong> by selecting one of the option under Object -> Transform in object mode:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Geometry to origin</em></li>\n<li><em>Origin to geometry</em></li>\n<li><em>Origin to 3D cursor</em></li>\n<li><em>Origin to Center of mass (surface)</em></li>\n<li><em>Origin to center of mass (volume)</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/413c2d235bd5b17966a0c236455f49d0/c58a3/blender-change-origin-objects-1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.859649122807014%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Object transform\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/413c2d235bd5b17966a0c236455f49d0/0470c/blender-change-origin-objects-1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/413c2d235bd5b17966a0c236455f49d0/6c669/blender-change-origin-objects-1.jpg 285w,\n/static/413c2d235bd5b17966a0c236455f49d0/882a4/blender-change-origin-objects-1.jpg 570w,\n/static/413c2d235bd5b17966a0c236455f49d0/0470c/blender-change-origin-objects-1.jpg 1140w,\n/static/413c2d235bd5b17966a0c236455f49d0/c58a3/blender-change-origin-objects-1.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Object transform</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>When we want to transform a group of objects at once we have a number of options to change the pivot point of the\nselection. We can choose it by selecting one of the option available from the list near the 3D transform manipulator\nwidget.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1140px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3f7d5fbb79f4b0fe63eb8ce9c676fd3a/c58a3/blender-change-pivot-objects-1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.859649122807014%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Pivot Change\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/3f7d5fbb79f4b0fe63eb8ce9c676fd3a/0470c/blender-change-pivot-objects-1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/3f7d5fbb79f4b0fe63eb8ce9c676fd3a/6c669/blender-change-pivot-objects-1.jpg 285w,\n/static/3f7d5fbb79f4b0fe63eb8ce9c676fd3a/882a4/blender-change-pivot-objects-1.jpg 570w,\n/static/3f7d5fbb79f4b0fe63eb8ce9c676fd3a/0470c/blender-change-pivot-objects-1.jpg 1140w,\n/static/3f7d5fbb79f4b0fe63eb8ce9c676fd3a/c58a3/blender-change-pivot-objects-1.jpg 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1140px) 100vw, 1140px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Pivot Change</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>That's all for selection and transform of objects. In the next post we will start to explore the art of modeling in\nBlender.</p>"}